<title>BELGIUM: CHASE MANHATTAN CONFIRMS TO BE BELFOX MARKET-MAKER.</title>
<headline>CHASE MANHATTAN CONFIRMS TO BE BELFOX MARKET-MAKER.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>London-based Chase Manhattan Bank said on Thursday it would become a market-maker in short-term interest rate contracts on the Belgian Futures and Options exchange, Belfox, from next Tuesday.</p>
<p>The bank will be the first London-based market-maker to set up a direct link to the Belfox trading system. Deals will be carried out via computer terminals based in London, it said.</p>
<p>&quot;This move demonstrates Chase's ability to compete on a global scale and at the same time show commitment to local European markets,&quot; Rob Standing, the bank's head of trading in London, said in the statement.</p>
<p>Banking sources named Chase Manhattan last month as a future market maker after Belfox had said it was in talks with three London houses.</p>
